"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"I've run into this several times between Twitter users and TG users where someone will mistakenly think in order to get bETH, they have to first go from ETH to stETH.   This isn't strictly necessary.   If you already have some stETH, and want to use it in Anchor, then you can certainly convert to bETH.   However, you can reduce fees by simply converting your ETH straight to bETH in a single transaction.\\n\\nI'll walk you through this right quick.\\n\\nFirst, head over to [https://anchor.lido.fi](https://anchor.lido.fi/) and then connect your wallet containing ETH you with to convert to bETH. I used MetaMask.\\n\\nOnce your Ethereum wallet is connected, click the drop-down and change from stETH to ETH.   You are now able to select an amount of ETH you with to convert.\\n\\n![](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/1esyECCcR1sAqztJZ6ftB.png?height=126&width=309)\\n\\n\",\"timestamp\":1638353688,\"title\":\"\\nGo Straight from ETH to bETH\"},\"digest\":\"Ico7zWkBmKe8SW6pQFEuXDJ9XIFYVsJLvMbNGjPmZIM\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0xd1c15D0AB8c5709407c9f199a9Dbe977C41cC740\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"PbCB3mu0e9rAahWN4dqB2lBeTjZHSpRp-Ym_hIr9L5s\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"JCe9KZeRgU6g54ICPPqQbQMEOgFgyMiNjaJDrAcWEWY\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"-dNqbYUT_sX_zsc8HM8g9mzTI4DdILOzQzpPouMKVwDGPHEy_cQebNC6_2BBOR72AyJwz5B2D09suImT2F7fiQ\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0xe8133a2208a06cc13c570564b0fc399a454af8c9b12627dd72d1edee0b077f24241ca17446fa629cfd351f38ffb1694b5105785567abe211907b73880ef14f6c1c\",\"signingKeyMessage\":\"I authorize publishing on mirror.xyz from this device using:\\n{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"PbCB3mu0e9rAahWN4dqB2lBeTjZHSpRp-Ym_hIr9L5s\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"JCe9KZeRgU6g54ICPPqQbQMEOgFgyMiNjaJDrAcWEWY\\\"}\",\"algorithm\":{\"name\":\"ECDSA\",\"hash\":\"